Bank of Japan’s Noda to Serve as Chair in Absence of Chiefs

-- B y   T a k e h i k o   K u m a k u r a   a n d   M a y u m i   O t s u m a
-- 
2011-04-05T03:14:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/bank-of-japan-s-noda-to-serve-as-chair-in-absence-of-chiefs-1-.html
Tadao Noda, a  Bank of Japan (8301)  board
member, will act as chairman of the bank’s policy board in the
event that Governor Masaaki Shirakawa and Deputy Governors
Hirohide Yamaguchi and Kiyohiko Nishimura can’t serve in that
capacity, the central bank said in a statement today.  Noda, 64, took over the role from Miyako Suda, who retired
from the board on March 31.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
